wikipedia_page.main: Martin Woosnam (1903–1962) was an English amateur football centre half who played in the Football League for Thames and Brentford. He captained the England amateur international team and was later capped by Wales at the same level.

response: * Martin Woosnam (1903–1962) Welsh amateur international footballer, played for Thames A.F.C. and Brentford F.C.
